   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting" image="QN_Npc_Scholar_Baily.dds" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-a" mid="7" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>What's the matter?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="6"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>This is terrible...<BR>(He looks quite worried.)</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-b" mid="9" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>That's not normal?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="8"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholars Heraldry Scholar Bailey${action:Talk}<BR>Ah, {user_class} {user_nick}. Listen up...<BR>After clearing some monsters, the strong ones will appear randomly.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-c" mid="11" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Maybe you can elaborate more...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="10"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Normal...What? No.. No! Why would it...<BR>We need to know why this is happening. Can I count you?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-accepting-acceptted" mid="19" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html><FONT color=#086171>Accept Quest</FONT></html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="18"><![CDATA[<html>$Secrets of the Abyss$</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-1-a" mid="84" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Thick mist? Abyss? </html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="20"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>The areas have changed, and covered in a thick mist. We have observe this mist, together with the strength of the monsters that indicates the influence of the Abyss.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-1-b" mid="86" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>How can I help?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="85"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>We need the details and effects. That's the main reason I need your help.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-1-c" mid="89" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="87"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>I guess the clues can be found in the jewels of those affected monsters. I might learn more if I could study them.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-1-d" mid="91" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Yes. Quite a list...</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="90"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey${action:Talk}<BR>Yes. I'll need the strongest jewel, Lydia's from the Raider's Den, Coldtime Harpy's from the Sigh Canyon, or Vepres's at the Forest Sanctuary.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="95"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>I only need one...but there's something else.<BR>Facing the Abyss by yourself is suicide..Please find some comrades to accompany you.<BR>(A party is recommended for Abyss mode.)</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-2" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="29"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>You must enter the Abyss at the Raider's Den, the Sigh Canyon, or the Forest Sanctuary to acquire strong jewel. Remember, to challenge the Abyss and find them!<BR>(A party is recommended for Abyss mode.)</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-3" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-3-a" mid="60" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Here it is.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="59"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>You're back. Did you bring the jewel?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-3-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-3-b" mid="62" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>How could that happen?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="61"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>Fantastic... (He examines the jewel intently.)<BR>As expected... this jewel has mutated...</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-3-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-3-c" mid="64" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="63"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey${action:Talk}<BR>You know the story of how our world, Lagendia, was created?<BR>It's said that our world was formed in the pure dreams of the Goddess Altea.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-3-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-3-d" mid="66" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="65"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>The dark Goddess.. Vestinel poisoned Altea, jealous of the world she creates. While Altea sleeps eternally now, as the poison invades her dreams turned into horrendous nightmares.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-3-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-3-e" mid="79" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>That would mean that the Abyss is...?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="77"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>It's possible that odd occurances could be caused by the nightmares of the Goddess.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n028_scholar_bailey-3-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n028_scholar_bailey-3-f" mid="81" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Is there something we can do?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="80"><![CDATA[<html>$Heraldry Scholar Bailey$<BR>The Abyss is likely the direct manifestations of the nightmares... Its connected to the nature of our world would explain how it can cause such mutations in the land and creatures.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
